            <div type="typology">
               <p rend="typology">West (Maghreb) › Algeria › Western dialects</p>
               <p>Pre-Hilalian-type village dialect</p>
            </div>

            <div type="general">
               <p>Ghazaouet is a small fishing port in northwest Algeria at the foot of the Trara mountain range. It has a long history. During the Roman period the town was called Ad Fratres. In the 19th century the French founded the settlement of Nemours at the location of today’s town. It served as a military supply post during the war with Morocco.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p>The dialect of Ghazaouet is still poorly investigated. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:96YK24BH">Siagh (1976)</rs> offers some information on the phonology and provides morpho-syntactic and lexical comparative data with the dialects of Oran and Tlemcen. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:9EIJJNHS">Hocini (2010-2011)</rs> is a sociolinguistic study on phonological, morphological, and lexical variation in the dialects of Ghazaoet and nearby villages.</p>
            </div>
